---
/**
 * Accessibility statement — public-facing conformance + feedback page.
 *
 * Linked from every page footer (Phase 1c build punch-list item #10).
 * Required sections per Phase 1c lock: conformance target, date last reviewed,
 * known issues, compatibility statement, feedback mechanism, technical specs,
 * assessment approach.
 *
 * Length target: 400–600 words. Update `lastReviewed` whenever the site is
 * audited or substantively changed.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastReviewed = '2026-05-06';
const title = 'Accessibility — Mountain Dog Consulting';
const description = 'How Mountain Dog Consulting designs and tests this site for accessibility, what we conform to, and how to send feedback.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Accessibility statement</h1>

    <p>
      Mountain Dog Consulting is committed to making this website usable by as many people
      as possible, including people who use assistive technology to read, navigate, or
      interact with the web. Accessibility is part of the work, not an afterthought.
    </p>

    <h2>Conformance target</h2>
    <p>
      This site is designed to conform to the
      <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/" rel="external">
        Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2
      </a>
      at Level AA. Several Level AAA criteria are also met where the design choices made
      AAA conformance essentially free — body-text contrast, focus appearance, heading
      structure, and respect for reduced-motion preferences. The conformance target is
      ratified internationally as ISO/IEC 40500:2025.
    </p>

    <h2>Last reviewed</h2>
    <p>
      This statement and the underlying site were last reviewed on <time datetime={lastReviewed}>{lastReviewed}</time>.
      A formal review is scheduled with every substantive content or template change.
    </p>

    <h2>Assessment approach</h2>
    <p>
      Conformance is verified using a combination of automated and manual testing on
      every change before it is published:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>axe-core and Pa11y run against every build in continuous integration</li>
      <li>Lighthouse Accessibility score is held at 100 as a deploy gate</li>
      <li>Manual keyboard-only walkthroughs cover every interactive element</li>
      <li>Screen-reader testing pairs VoiceOver with Safari (macOS and iOS) and NVDA with Firefox and Chrome (Windows)</li>
      <li>Colour contrast for every shipping text-on-background combination is verified against the WCAG 2.x relative-luminance formula and meets at least 4.5:1; body text combinations meet 7:1</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Known issues</h2>
    <p>
      No outstanding accessibility defects are known at the date above. Issues identified
      after review are tracked in the public source repository and fixed in the next
      deploy. If you encounter a barrier, please report it (see <a href="#feedback">Feedback</a>
      below).
    </p>

    <h2>Compatibility</h2>
    <p>
      The site is built and tested to work with current versions of major web browsers
      (the most recent two releases of Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge) and the
      following assistive technologies:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>VoiceOver on macOS and iOS</li>
      <li>NVDA on Windows</li>
      <li>TalkBack on Android</li>
      <li>Voice Control on macOS and iOS, Voice Access on Android, and Dragon NaturallySpeaking on Windows</li>
      <li>Switch Control, switch interfaces, and on-screen keyboards on each platform</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The site does not require JavaScript to read or navigate. Cookies are not used.
      Layouts respect a user's <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> and zoom settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Technical specifications</h2>
    <p>
      The site is a static HTML site authored in markdown and built with the Astro static
      site generator. Pages are served from a content delivery network with no client-side
      scripting on content pages. Typography uses the Atkinson Hyperlegible font, designed
      by the Braille Institute for low-vision readability, with a system-font fallback.
    </p>

    <h2 id="feedback">Feedback</h2>
    <p>
      If you encounter a barrier on this site or have a suggestion for improvement, please
      write to
      <a href="mailto:accessibility@mountaindogconsulting.com">
        accessibility@mountaindogconsulting.com
      </a>.
      Reports are welcome by any format that suits you — plain email, screenshot, screen
      recording, or a phone call. I aim to acknowledge every report within two business
      days and to fix or formally respond to issues within thirty days. If a fix will take
      longer, you'll get an interim plan.
    </p>

    <h2>Source</h2>
    <p>
      The source code for this site is public at
      <a href="https://github.com/disabledtech/mountaindogconsulting-site" rel="external">
        github.com/disabledtech/mountaindogconsulting-site
      </a>. Issues and pull requests are welcome.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
